The dashboard page should present an overview of key metrics and summaries related to various modules.
The dashboard should be prominently displayed as the main landing page of the admin interface.
The metrics and summaries should be organized in a visually appealing and easy-to-understand manner.
Each module summary should include relevant information such as the total count, percentage, or any other relevant data.
The module summaries should be accompanied by meaningful icons or visuals to enhance the user experience.
The dashboard should provide clickable links or buttons that allow users to navigate to the respective module or section for further details.
The graphs, such as pie charts, bar charts, line charts, etc., should be visually appealing and provide a clear representation of data.
The graphs should be interactive, allowing users to hover over or click on data points to view specific details.
The graphs should be responsive and adjust appropriately to different screen sizes and devices.
The dashboard page should have a consistent color palette and typography that aligns with the overall visual style of the admin interface.
The dashboard should be optimized for performance, ensuring fast loading times even when handling large data sets.
The dashboard should provide options for users to customize the displayed metrics and summaries based on their preferences or specific requirements.
The design of the dashboard should prioritize relevant and actionable information, avoiding clutter or unnecessary elements.
The dashboard should be accessible, meeting WCAG 2.1 guidelines for color contrast, keyboard navigation, and screen reader compatibility.
The dashboard should be tested across different browsers and devices to ensure a consistent experience for all users.
The dashboard should include appropriate data visualization techniques to effectively communicate trends, comparisons, or patterns within the data.
The dashboard page should be regularly updated with real-time or near real-time data to provide accurate and up-to-date information.
The dashboard should include clear labels, headings, and descriptions to assist users in understanding the displayed metrics and graphs.
